.nh
.TH "SYMAIRA" "1" "May 2026" "Symaira Vault" "OpenPass Manual"

.SH NAME
symaira-setup - Interactive setup wizard for OpenPass


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBsymaira setup [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Launch the interactive setup wizard to initialize or re-configure your vault.

.PP
The wizard guides you through:
  • Vault directory and passphrase
  • Authentication method (Touch ID or passphrase)
  • Sync strategy (local or git remote)
  • Multi-device setup hints
  • Additional recipients for shared access
  • AI agent (MCP) configuration
  • Backup recommendations
  • Profile name

.PP
For non-interactive environments (CI, scripts), use 'openpass init' instead.


.SH OPTIONS
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for setup

.PP
\fB--keep-on-error\fP[=false]
	do not rollback vault init artifacts when subsequent steps fail

.PP
\fB--no-resume\fP[=false]
	disable setup resume after abort


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--color\fP="auto"
	When to emit ANSI color: auto, always, never

.PP
\fB--no-pipe-warning\fP[=false]
	suppress 'reading from non-TTY' warning when piping secrets

.PP
\fB--output\fP="text"
	Output format (text, json, yaml)

.PP
\fB--profile\fP=""
	use a named vault profile

.PP
\fB--quiet\fP[=false]
	suppress non-error output

.PP
\fB--theme\fP=""
	Color preset: default, highcontrast, colorblind (or OPENPASS_THEME)

.PP
\fB--vault\fP="~/.openpass"
	path to the password vault


.SH EXAMPLE
.EX
  # Run the wizard (resumes from saved state if available)
  openpass setup

  # Restart from scratch
  openpass setup --no-resume

  # Keep partial vault artifacts on error for debugging
  openpass setup --keep-on-error
.EE


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBopenpass(1)\fP
